  "name": "RPlog_Station_Destruction_Training",
  "title": "Live-Fire Over Selene",
  "summary": "Commodore Krieg convenes a joint Imperial training exercise pairing ISB Agent Dreven Mercurio against the pilots of the fleet. Briefed that it is a live-fire mission, Dreven must infiltrate a derelict space station near Selene, retrieve reactor data, and escape on foot while the bomber and fighter squadrons led by Liza Molokai and the squadron commander Dante work to destroy the station outright. As the assault begins, Krieg's hidden surprises emerge: an active defense grid, a collapsing reactor walkway that strands Dreven, drone fighters launched from a breakaway sensor tower, and a tractor beam that snares Wolf and Mirden's shuttle. Dreven scrambles through depressurizing corridors and a desperate leap to reach an escape pod just as the station is blown apart, then signals an Imperial SOS as Krieg himself drops in to test Dante's squadron before calling the exercise to a successful close. In the debrief, Krieg praises the participants, critiques their screening and escape planning, and discusses with Dante the value of signature 'razzle dazzle' maneuvers to instill fear in the enemy, with Dreven offering his own thoughts on intimidation.",
